33e4f741-3ce1-4470-91d7-923d75076cdf.do_description: To make the output, you have to...fill in the rectangles until only a one-square border of the original color remains.
33e4f741-3ce1-4470-91d7-923d75076cdf.grid_description: The output grid size...remains the same.
33e4f741-3ce1-4470-91d7-923d75076cdf.see_description: In the input, you should see...two large rectangles.

b63e53a9-c3d6-4b53-9a6c-c63b58e2ce86.do_description: To make the output, you have to... fill the inside of both shapes with red leaving a border the same color as original.
b63e53a9-c3d6-4b53-9a6c-c63b58e2ce86.grid_description: The output grid size... stay the same.
b63e53a9-c3d6-4b53-9a6c-c63b58e2ce86.see_description: In the input, you should see... a square and rectangular.

e8769a59-b2ed-413c-b8e6-467467999935.do_description: To make the output, you have to... color in the center of each gray square red, but make sure you leave a 1 square gray border around it (so if it's a 5x5 gray square, you would color a red 3x3 square inside it, leaving a gray border around the red square).
e8769a59-b2ed-413c-b8e6-467467999935.grid_description: The output grid size... will be the same size as the input grid (10x10).
e8769a59-b2ed-413c-b8e6-467467999935.see_description: In the input, you should see... two gray rectangles.
